  "description": "Light is electromagnetic radiation: oscillating electric and magnetic fields that propagate through space at a fixed speed, approximately 300,000 kilometers per second in vacuum. This speed -- denoted $c$ -- is the fastest that any signal, particle, or information can travel.",
